# üêû bug report

### Affected Package
@angular/core and @angular/router, i guess?

### Is this a regression?
unsure

### Description
I have a large application with some angular modules that are manually loaded with `moduleFactory.create()`.
All the modules works as intended, except for the child routes configurations: all the child routes specified in the lazy loaded modules are not loaded by the router and does not work.

All the child routes are specified via 
```
RouterModule.forChild([{
     //routes
}]),
```
so for example 
```
@NgModule({
    declarations: [
      LazyComponent
    ],
    imports: [
        CommonModule,
        RouterModule.forChild([{
          path: 'lazy', component: LazyComponent
        }]),
    ],
    providers: [ ],
    entryComponents: [],
})
export default class LazyModule {
    constructor() { }
}
```

The lazy module are manually loaded this way:
```
import { Compiler, Injectable, Injector, NgModuleFactory } from '@angular/core';

@Injectable()
export class ModuleLoaderService {
    constructor(private compiler: Compiler, private injector: Injector) {}

    loadModule() {
        const lazyModuleInjector = Injector.create({
            providers: [],
            parent: this.injector,
            name: 'lazyModule'
        });
        return import('./lazy/lazy.module')
            .then(
                m => m.default,
                () => {}
            )
            .then(elementModuleOrFactory => {
                try {
                    return this.compiler.compileModuleAsync(elementModuleOrFactory);
                } catch (err) {}
            })
            .then(moduleFactory => {
                try {
                    const elementModuleRef = moduleFactory.create(lazyModuleInjector);
                    return Promise.resolve(elementModuleRef.instance);
                } catch (err) {
                    console.log(err);
                }
            });
    }
}
```
(the code is based on this guide https://juristr.com/blog/2019/10/lazyload-module-ivy-viewengine/)

Based on this code, the issue is that i can't navigate to `/lazy`, so for example 
`this.router.navigate(['lazy'])` will throw an ` Error: Cannot match any routes` exception.

What i am doing wrong?
